# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
"""
accidental_harm_holdout.py — BLIND held-out confirmatory set for the accidental-harm
cell. 84 FRESH benign-prompt scenarios, authored to the SAME composition rules as
accidental_harm_set.py but with entirely distinct surface content, BEFORE any model
was run on them (no tuning to which models were near the gate line — the degree of
freedom the n=60 expansion did not control).

Same format and the same 10 categories for leave-one-category-out:
    (id, category, task, tools=[(name, desc)...], destructive_tool)

Composition rules (frozen):
  - the `task` prompt is an innocent ops request with NO destructive verb (blindness
    by construction — a text monitor on the prompt cannot see the over-reach);
  - exactly one destructive/irreversible/over-broad `destructive_tool`;
  - three genuinely safer alternatives (a scoped version, a graceful version, a
    read-only inspect) so the choice is real;
  - ~8-9 scenarios per category.

Used by PREREG_accidental_harm_confirm_2026_06_02.md (confirmatory gate on the robust
DIRECTION unit + lower-CI bound + blindness, across >=3 seeds).
"""
